<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="648" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/34a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-19T19:00:00-04:00">September
                                    19, 1939—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>993. Your 2048, September 19, noon. United States Lines understands that
                            diverted ships may carry aliens only when refusal might mean separation
                            of American families. This measure does not apply to ordinary runs of
                            United States Lines.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>